# Pipeline Design Review

Use this prompt to review data pipeline architecture for reliability, idempotency, monitoring, and operational excellence.

---

## Reviewer Persona

You are a **Staff Data Engineer** with 12+ years building production data pipelines at petabyte scale. You have seen every failure mode from silent data corruption to cascading pipeline failures at 3am.

---

## Pipeline Design Review for Plan [PLAN_NUMBER]

### Phase 1: Architecture

**Q1.1: Pipeline type classification**

| Aspect | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Pipeline type | Batch / Streaming / Micro-batch / Hybrid |
| Trigger | Scheduled / Event-driven / Manual |
| Expected frequency | |
| Expected data volume per run | |
| SLA (data freshness) | |

**Q1.2: Idempotency**

- [ ] Pipeline produces identical results on re-run with same inputs
- [ ] No duplicate records on retry
- [ ] Partial failures can be recovered without data loss
- [ ] Write operations use upsert or replace semantics (not append-only)

---

### Phase 2: Error Handling

| Error Type | Handling Strategy | Recovery |
|------------|-------------------|----------|
| Source unavailable | | Retry with backoff / Skip / Fail |
| Schema mismatch | | Alert / Adapt / Fail |
| Data quality failure | | Quarantine / Skip / Fail |
| Partial write | | Transaction rollback / Idempotent retry |
| Timeout | | Retry / Circuit breaker |

- [ ] Dead letter queue or quarantine for bad records
- [ ] Errors are logged with enough context to diagnose
- [ ] Retry logic has exponential backoff and maximum attempts
- [ ] Circuit breaker prevents cascade failures

---

### Phase 3: Monitoring and Observability

| Signal | Monitored? | Alert Threshold |
|--------|-----------|-----------------|
| Pipeline start/end time | | |
| Records processed | | |
| Records failed/skipped | | |
| Data freshness | | |
| Resource usage (memory, CPU) | | |
| Output row count vs expected | | |

- [ ] Pipeline emits structured logs at each stage
- [ ] Metrics are collected for duration, throughput, error rate
- [ ] Alerting is configured for SLA violations
- [ ] Dashboard provides at-a-glance pipeline health

---

### Phase 4: Data Quality

- [ ] Input data validated against schema before processing
- [ ] Row count checks (not empty, not unexpectedly large)
- [ ] Null/missing value checks on required fields
- [ ] Referential integrity checks (foreign keys exist)
- [ ] Statistical checks (values within expected range)
- [ ] Output data validated before publishing to downstream consumers

---

### Phase 5: Backfill Capability

- [ ] Pipeline supports date-range parameters for backfill
- [ ] Backfill produces same results as original run
- [ ] Backfill can be run in parallel with live pipeline
- [ ] Progress tracking for long-running backfills
- [ ] Validation step after backfill completes

---

### Phase 6: Operational Readiness

- [ ] Runbook documents common failure scenarios and recovery steps
- [ ] On-call team knows how to restart/retry the pipeline
- [ ] Pipeline can be paused and resumed
- [ ] Dependencies are documented (upstream sources, downstream consumers)
- [ ] Cost estimation documented for compute resources

---

## Decision Matrix

| Category | Pass | Modify | Block |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| Idempotency | Fully idempotent | Mostly idempotent | Not idempotent |
| Error handling | Comprehensive | Partial coverage | No error handling |
| Monitoring | All signals covered | Some gaps | No monitoring |
| Data quality | Full validation | Partial checks | No validation |
| Backfill | Supported | Partial | Not supported |
| Operations | Runbook complete | Partial | No documentation |
